prediction.overall_explanation: The library handles complex signature recovery, including Merkle proofs, chained updates, and custom types. Parsing uses safe library functions. External calls (ERC1271, Sapient) are view and validated. Chained recovery has a logic error returning root config values instead of target payload's, potentially breaking legitimate chained sigs (DoS for users), but validation requires proper signatures per link, preventing unauthorized access or fund loss. No overflows, reentrancy, or access control issues. Keccak security assumed.
